  "prompt": "In this WordPress era, why do people still study coding instead of just using it?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why people continue to study coding despite the availability of user-friendly platforms like WordPress:\n\n1. Customization and Flexibility\n- WordPress has limitations\n- Custom coding allows complete control over functionality\n- Developers can create unique solutions not possible with pre-built themes/plugins\n\n2. Career Opportunities\n- High demand for skilled programmers\n- Better job prospects and higher salaries\n- Ability to work in various industries (web, mobile, AI, etc.)\n\n3. Understanding Technology\n- Coding provides deeper understanding of how technology works\n- Enables problem-solving and critical thinking skills\n- Allows creation of custom tools and solutions\n\n4. Advanced Web Development\n- Complex web applications require custom coding\n- Frameworks like React, Angular, Vue.js need programming skills\n- E-commerce, SaaS platforms often require custom development\n\n5. Performance and Optimization\n- Custom code can be more efficient than pre-built solutions\n- Better control over website/application performance\n- Ability to optimize for specific requirements\n\n6. Innovation and Creativity\n- Coding allows creation of entirely new technologies\n- Enables development of unique software and applications\n- Provides platform for technological innovation\n\n7. Security and Control\n- Custom solutions offer more robust security\n- Greater control over data and functionality\n- Reduced dependency on third-party platforms\n\nWhile WordPress is great for many scenarios, coding remains a valuable skill with broad applications.",
